My meme

My meme is a photo of Gru from Despicable Me holding a gun to the camera and pretending to shoot the reader because their p-value is insignificant. I love minions and find the photo of Gru so funny, and I always get confused whether the p-value being greater or less than 0.05 makes it insignificant, so I made this creative meme to help me remember.

My meme

install.packages("magick")
library(magick)

# adds background image
gru <- image_read("gruface.jpg") 

# add top text
gru_top <- image_annotate(gru, "YOUR P-VALUE IS > 0.05?", size = 20, gravity = "north", color = "white", strokecolor = "black")

# add bottom text
gru_bottom <- image_annotate(gru_top, "GOODBYE.", size = 36, gravity = "south", color = "white", strokecolor = "black")

# view the meme
gru_bottom

# give the meme a name
gru_bottom %>% image_write("my_meme.png")

My animation

My animation is a bunch of spirals in rainbow order. I am pretending to hypnotize you (the marker) into giving me a good grade with a pretty and hypnotic GIF. I think it’s creative because the brief didn’t say we had to add words to it but I still did, and I used more frames than needed.

My animation

#install.packages("magick")
library(magick)
# adding the 7 images
gif_images <- c("gif1.jpg", "gif2.jpg", "gif3.jpg", "gif4.jpg", "gif5.jpg", "gif6.jpg", "gif7.jpg")

# read images, create object
image_list <- image_read(gif_images)

fps <- 100
loop <- 0

# Create the GIF 
animation <- image_animate(image_list, fps = fps, loop = loop)
animation

# Add words to the GIF
animation_words <- image_annotate(animation, "hypnotising my way to a good grade", size = 16, gravity = "center", color = "white", strokecolor = "black")
animation_words
animation %>% image_write("my_animation.gif")
image_write(animation_words, "myanimation.gif")
